# Python Web App

This is a simple web app built using Python and Flask. It allows you to send GET and POST requests with a text input box.

## Requirements

- Python 3
- Flask

## Usage

1. Clone the repository to your local machine:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/python-web-app.git
```

2. Install the Flask package using pip:

```bash
pip install flask
```

3. Start the Flask server by running the `app.py` file:

```bash
python app.py
```

4. Open a web browser and go to [http://localhost:5000](http://localhost:5000). You should see a web page with a text input box and two buttons: "GET" and "POST".

5. To send a GET request, enter some text in the input box and click the "GET" button. The text you entered will be sent as a query parameter in the URL, and you should see a message with the text you entered.

6. To send a POST request, enter some text in the input box and click the "POST" button. The text you entered will be sent as the body of the request, and you should see a message with the text you entered.

That's it! You have successfully used the Python web app to send GET and POST requests with a text input box.

## Customization

You can customize the web app by modifying the `app.py` file and the `index.html` file.

To modify the server-side code, open the `app.py` file and update the `get_data` and `post_data` functions as needed.

To modify the client-side code, open the `index.html` file and update the HTML and JavaScript code as needed.

